Habitat.
Variety of habitats, including open woodland, low saltbush (
Atriplex spp.
) and bluebush (
Maireana spp.
) shrublands, tussock and spinifex (7riodia spp., 
Poaceae
) grasslands on clay or sandy soils, gibber (desert pavement) plain, and farmlands in southern regions. Distribution of Fat-tailed Dunnarts extends from relatively moist regions near the southern coast of Australia through the arid inland to inhospitable plains of the Lake Eyre Basin.
